trend_summary: Across the image series, slow infill converts scattered farmland into housing estates and small commercial pads, mainly along the central highway and southern grid. No large industrial zones or high-rise blocks emerge. Tree cover expands on unused parcels and around the north-eastern reservoir, slightly balancing impervious growth. Overall change is gradual and low-intensity.
notable_changes: Emergence of several cul-de-sac residential clusters on former pasture south-central and west.
New commercial/warehouse pads along the main east-west highway corridor.
Progressive reforestation of idle fields, especially north-east near the reservoir.
Minor widening and realignment of the principal highway, with clearer right-of-way.
